      <tr>
        <td bgcolor="dimgray" valign="top">
        <font color="white" face="Verdana, Arial, Helvetica" size="2">
        
		<a href="pop_profile.asp?mode=display&id=471">
        	
		<font color="white" face="Verdana, Arial, Helvetica" size="2"><b>Ancagalon</a>
        </b></font>

        <br><font color="white" face="Verdana, Arial, Helvetica" size="1"><small>Decaying Skeleton</small></font>

        <br>
        <br>
        <br><font color="white" face="Verdana, Arial, Helvetica" size="1"><small>Canada</small></font>
        <br><font color="white" face="Verdana, Arial, Helvetica" size="1"><small>52 Posts</small></font></td>
        <td bgcolor="dimgray" colspan="2" ><img src="icon_posticon.gif" border="0" hspace="3"><font color="white" face="Verdana, Arial, Helvetica" size="1">Posted&nbsp;-&nbsp;05/11/2001&nbsp;:&nbsp; 17:30:33</font>

        
		&nbsp;<a href="pop_profile.asp?mode=display&id=471"><img src="icon_profile.gif" height=15 width=15 alt="Show Profile" border="0" align="absmiddle" hspace="6"></a>
        
			&nbsp;<a href="JavaScript:openWindow('pop_mail.asp?id=471')"><img src="icon_email.gif" height=15 width=15 alt="Email Poster" border="0" align="absmiddle" hspace="6"></a>

        &nbsp;<a href="post.asp?method=TopicQuote&TOPIC_ID=4814&FORUM_ID=1&CAT_ID=1&Forum_Title=General+Discussions&Topic_Title=My+Findings+on+Holgresh+Elder+Beads"><img src="icon_reply_topic.gif" height=15 width=15 alt="Reply with Quote" border="0" align="absmiddle" hspace="6"></a>

        <hr noshade size="1">
        
        <font color="white" face="Verdana, Arial, Helvetica" size="2">A 49+ necro can do this alone, but it can be tricky at times. Set up in the tunnel at about one third of the way into the tunnel to the Holgresh Cave (closer to the exit outside then the Holgresh cave). Pet up and fully buff Jaboner.</P><P>Go to the cave and target the closest Holgresh. Pull with engulphing/dooming and run to your pet. If the Holgresh you pulled had a pet, the pet will make it to you way before its master. Just Invoke Fear their pets. As long as fear does not break early, they run far enough away not to come back.</P><P>By then, the Holgresh should be coming down the tunnel. Lead with a cancel magic to get rid of their nasty damage shields. Sick pet, Invoke Fear and lay on a fast-DOT. Most of the Holgresh are green, and drop before they wander out of the tunnel. The Elders seem to have a few more HPs, so lay on another DOT or soften them up with a couple Ignite Bones.</P><P>The real pain is when they fall under the world, which seems to happen quite often. Bascially, use the same theory to kill them (you can still cast on them, and Jaboner can still hit them), but they will leave no corpse.</P><P>There are quite a few Holgresh in the cave, so you will need a couple mates to break and hold the entire cave. None of the Holgresh seem to see invisible, so you can scout the area in safety.</P><P>It is of course the Elders you are after for the Elder Beads. Any Holgresh can also drop a Strong Stick (or something like that) for the quest for the right click DD braclet. Also, the +20STR gloves (No Drop, Warrior only) seem to be a common drop off a Holgresh Raider. The raiders can be found in the cave and wandering outside, but the Elders only seem to spawn in the cave.</P><P>So what the heck does a necro need with an Eye of Zomm you ask? I have not done a lot of experimentation with them as of yet, but here is what I found:</P><P>You cannot have a pet up and cast an eye.<BR>The eye lasts about 30 seconds.<BR>Anyone can attack / cast on the eye (the eye has 1 HP).<BR>Anyone can cast invisible / undead invisible on the eye. <BR>You can cast spells when the eye is up. <BR>You can cast Feign Death / cast Gather Shadows / Undead Invis and the eye does NOT suicide.<BR>You can target and con creatures through the eye.</P><P>So, the primary use for the eye is to give necros something to tap / Bond / Vex when there is nothing else around to tap. There are a lot of creatures that necros cannot land taps on. No tapping, means no Lich, means no pacting, means no mana transfer. Even when we cannot land spells on the creature our group is fighting, we can still function in a support role (granted these are not the sexiest things necros do, but hey, it is a fact of life). If a necro finds himself in this situation and the group is allowing pets, just give the beads to a non-pet member of the group and have him / her recast the eye for you to tap. </P><P>The second thing the eye is good for is scouting an area. Cast eye, and then Feign Death. Go take a quick peek around a blind corner. Go Con the creatures in a crowded room. I need to do a bit more experimentation with this, but it is my understanding that when you get off a successful Feign Death, you cannot wrack up any NEW agro. So, if nothing is agro on you before hand, cast an eye, cast Feign Death, scoot into the room with the eye, have the creatures kill the eye, then stand up safely without having the creatures agro on you. </P><P>The third thing the eye might be good for would be to pull stuff. I am not sure what kind of situation you would want to use an eye to pull things, but it would allow a player to agro creatures from a distance. Since you are not causing damage on the creature, or are not casting an offensive spell to pull, you will have a minimal amount of built up hate. Again, I have not really experimented with pulling things with the eye, but I could really see a skillful monk coming up with some creative ways to use the eye in conjunction with Feign Death to pull some tough areas. </P><P>In summary, Elder Beads definitely are a neat little item to carry around. Granted, they will not be useful everywhere, but they are a powerful little tool in the right situation. </P><P>Cheers,<BR>Ancagalon the Black</P><P> </font></td>
      </tr>

